Interface IPreferencesModel

All Known Implementing Classes:
PreferencesModel
public interface IPreferencesModel
Defines the behavior of a preferences model for managing application preferences. Allows setting and retrieving preferences using key-value pairs.

  • Method Details

    • setPreference

      void setPreference(String key, String value) throws IOException
      Sets a preference value associated with the given key.
      Parameters:
      key - the key of the preference to be set
      value - the value to be associated with the given key
      Throws:
      IOException - if there is an error while saving the preference

    • getPreference

      Optional<Object> getPreference(String key)
      Retrieves the value of a preference associated with the given key.
      Parameters:
      key - the key of the preference to retrieve
      Returns:
      an Optional containing the value of the preference if found, or Optional.empty() if not found
